Homa Bay Town MP Peter Kaluma is currently recording a statement over his fight with rival Washington Ogaga during a political rally.Police had given the two 24 hours to record the statements, following the incident that saw MPs demand tight security amid campaigns for the 2017 general election.Kaluma arrived at Homa Bay police station accompanied by some politicians and his supporters.The vocal opposition lawmaker and frequent House debater, was kicked, punched and wrestled to the ground by Ogaga, who will vie for his seat in the 2017 poll.He told the National Assembly that he survived death, during the session on Tuesday, during which MPs asked for tight security amid campaigns for the August 8, 2016 general election.Read: I nearly died in Homa Bay chaos, Kaluma says as MPs call for tight securityOgaga said on Wednesday that he had recorded his statement and obtained OB number 30/27/11/16.Kakamega Senator Bonny Khalwale said the fight between the duo was stupid and would not help either of them win the MP seat in next year's election.Read: Kaluma's stupid fight with Ogaga will not help MP race - KhalwaleAlso read: Ranguma's arm hurt after shameless MPs exchange blows in Homa Bay